  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guera Emergency Food Security Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CRS believes an approach using horticultural inputs, building back the livestock population, and &#x201C;keyhole&#x201D; gardens is the best method by which to address food insecurity and limited livelihood opportunities in the sub-Prefecture of Mongo. Seed and tool fairs hosted in October 2013 at the beginning of the  horticultural off-season will also help to build resilience and to protect against future shocks in the region. In addition, a distribution of female goats will help to rebuild the goat population after the Sahel food crisis in 2012.  The project will also introduce the keyhole garden technique which is a vegetable garden close to the household that uses only small amounts of water.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to aid the most vulnerable and food insecure households through improved livestock and horticultural inputs. Increased seed inputs will improve production yield and diet diversity of targeted beneficiaries, as well as the local economies of beneficiaries, as all materials for the project will be purchased from local vendors.</narrative>
  </description>
